message:
Add basic infrastructure
 * Adds code to create the VM and Docker images with Keras and Tensorflow
 * Adds code to spin up AWS EC2 to run programs on GPUs
 * This was copied from https://github.com/OpenTreeMap/open-tree-id

Update README files

* Get rid of scripts/download since all data gets stored on S3 from which it can be downloaded via the UI.
* Add a simple experiment file to test that things work

Rebrand project as raster-vision

* Change references to open-tree-id and keras-semantic-segmentation to raster-vision
* Inject the data_dir and s3_bucket as environment variables to make it easier for
other people to run the project
* Move ISPRS data to its own subdirectory
* Update deployment to run off the new R&D AWS account
* Update readme to describe new, broader focus of the project and to use the raster-vision name
Reduce repetition of RASTER_VISION_DATA_DIR in README.md

Make submit_jobs script handle dependencies between jobs

The script now sequences the jobs according to their dependencies and informs
AWS Batch about these dependencies. Since the script is more complex now, it
has been re-written in Python.

Add attempts as argument to submit_jobs script

By default, the job will be attempted five times in order to deal with spot instances that
get outbid. However, if running a job to see if it might fail, you should set the attempts to one.
Build Batch GPU worker AMIs with Packer

Remove semseg and tagging stuff

Also, pass AWS credentials to Docker container, and make it so the
batch_submit script can be run from inside the container.
Add old object detection tag to README
Update docs for running stuff outside Vagrant

Add travis scripts.

Builds and publishes containers to quay.io via Travis.

Fixes based on PR review.

- Remove unused variable from jupyter script.
- Check environment variables for each case of publish in .travis.yml
- Specify that travis publishes quay.io containers for each merge of a PR instead of each commit to deploy.
Removed Vagrant and AWS related files.
Update readme with travis and codecov
Remove release notice banner in README
Replace Tiny SpaceNet in Three Places [skip ci]

Remove refs to QGIS plugin

It was difficult to maintain and we weren't getting a lot of value out of it
Add new diagrams and move images to img/

Migrate from Travis to GitHub Actions (#1218)

* Rename build and publish scripts to STRTA conventions

* Create CI workflow

* Remove Travis env file sourcing from cibuild

* Move CI tests into cibuild script

* Move codecov into cibuild

* Stop running test containers with interactive TTY

* Create test script

* Add help documentation to cibuild

* Enable pseudo TTY for Docker commands

* Fix coverage configuration

An upgrade for the coverage package was necessary, along with fixing
some path references and volume mounts in the unit test container.

* Use Codecov Action instead of script

* Create release workflow to run cipublish

* Remove check for pytorch image type, interpolate IMAGE_TYPE

* Use Raster Vision Quay credentials for release

* Remove Travis config

* Run test script commands in Docker containers when on CI

* Remove obsolete release instructions

* Restrict Quay.io credentials to cipublish steps

* Add help documentation to cipublish

* Determine how to tag image in cipublish script

* Use double quotes consistently for shell conditional clauses

Switch from Gitter to Github Discussions

* Update various references to Gitter
* Remove some issue templates and direct to forum

update usages of vector sources

- Replace all instances of non-None default_class_id with ClassInferenceTransformer.
- Also add "class_id" property in all features in cc-label-full.json because it is used as a label store in one of the unit tests and it doesn't make sense to do class inference on a label store.
update contact and contributing sections [skip ci]
make the cv tasks image smaller [skip ci]
